rComments: He's an okay teacher but he does not care about student regulation at all. His quizzes are smart and help out the students a lot (grades) but in terms of actual teaching, I wasn't very happy with it :(

Had him for online lin alg during the COVID pandemic, literally the best math prof I've ever had. Explained topics crystal clear with pre-recorded lectures, exam was exactly like all of the dgd questions / past tests. Weekly quizzes were a breeze, just make a formula sheet, study it, and you're golden. Highest mark I've ever received with no effort
TRUST ME, HE's LITERALLY A HOMIE, TAKE HIS CLASS!

Best math prof I've had so far. Explains things clearly, records lectures beforehand so class time is more of a review/DGD. Weekly tests which are very fair and multiple choice. No midterms. As long as you keep on top of the material for each weeks quiz you're good. He clearly cared about his students and wanted us to succeed.

One of the nicest profs I've ever had. In class he explained the topics clearly. Posted practice problems that you would actually see on tests. Quickly responded to emails. Took suggestions from his students. I don't know what else to say, other than if you get the chance to take linear algebra with him, please do yourself a favor!

Best prof I had during covid by a mile, recorded his lectures before hand and posted them (unlike some profs I had). Explained the hardest concepts very well. He is a very fair prof and cares about the students, he doesn't just throw work at them and except them to work mindlessly to meet deadlines. A very good prof, 10/10 would take again.

Considering all the sudden changes to learning due to COVID, Ruaridh mastered online teaching. He was very caring and understanding about the difficulties of online learning and helped us through problems in the best way possible. His video lectures were very clear, and any questions we had, he was able to answer properly.

Out of all my profs that have to teach online classes bc of COVID, Ruaridh is THE BEST! He is very smart and great at explaining even the most complicated concepts. The way he conducts his online class is amazing and he's very fair and considerate when it comes to tests. Great guy, hes very reachable after class too. He will answer any question!
